page.title: 03WEST END GREEN
page.content: West End Green is a small, quiet village on the outskirts of Stratfield Saye. There is one tiny village shop that sells everything for the local house owner. There are two rows of houses in a small close. The population is roughly one hundred. The whole village is surrounded by picturesque countryside. There is one lovely pub called "The Four Horseshoes". Lovells farm is approximately 150 yards from the village shop. There is no local transport but there are train and bus routes in Bramley (a nearby village). There is plenty of wildlife around { {WEST END GREEN }. Wild flowers grow everywhere. There are a lot of wild animals. If you like a quiet life in an untouched village with character this is the place to go.
